{
  "texts": [
    "While there are no official reports highlighting the same for dialects, it is not far-fetched to consider that linguistic self-hatred will exist here as well.",
    "It is time to end this self-hatred and normalise speaking dialects.",
    "By doing so, people speaking dialects will become more enthusiastic about preserving their dialects and this will inevitably aid research on dialects, thereby positively impacting society.",
    "Dialects are closely tied to culture and such differences have not been captured explicitly beyond the works described in this paper.Fig. 2.2Fig.",
    "Number of relevant 'papers-per-year' for keywords 'dialects' and 'socio-cultural' in the ACL Anthology."
  ]
}